body:
Particularly after recursive simplification it is common to get dead conditions.  I see this in one random IR dump:

```
   sv.always posedge %clock  {
      sv.ifdef.procedural "SYNTHESIS"  {
      } else  {
        sv.if %false  {
          sv.fatal
        }
      }
    }
    sv.always posedge %clock  {
      sv.ifdef.procedural "SYNTHESIS"  {
      } else  {
        sv.if %false  {
          sv.fwrite "Assertion failed: 'A' channel carries an address illegal for the specified bank visibility\0A    at Monitor.scala:81 assert (visible(edge.address(bundle), bundle.source, edge), \22'A' channel carries an address illegal for the specified bank visibility\22)\0A"
        }
      }
    }
```

(the sv.always nodes aren't getting merged because lower2rtl is generating them instead of alwaysff).
